CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 1, 1955, pg. 14, reads: "Nice Gesture - Joseph (Joe) Robinson, proprietor of Crawford Grill 2, donates his check for $10, which he recently won in Courier's 'Lucky Auto Plate Game,' to the local branch of the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People. Mrs. Marion B. Jordon, executive secretary of the branch, graciously accepts. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Joseph "Joe" Robinson presenting check to Marion Bond Jordon for Pittsburgh branch of NAACP, in office of Crawford Grill, No. 2
